text: Don't get me wrong. I love CLINT "The Man" Eastwood to bits. But after "BIRD" (Charlie Parker), "INVICTUS" (Nelson Mandela), "J. EDGAR" (J . Edgar Hoover), "JERSEY BOYS" (The Four Seasons), "AMERICAN SNIPER" (Chris Kyle) and "recently"  "SULLY" (Captain Chesley "Sully" Sullenberger) I was very much looking forward not to see yet another biopic (or in this case "just" another "incredible" story based on true events) again. Because, no matter how courageous those guys were at that particular moment in time, for me personally, that whole "event" is just not that dramatic enough, to make a feature-lenght movie about. Still, having said all that, I really do hope Mister Eastwood (88 next year!) will eventually prove me double wrong, and that "THE 15:17 TO PARIS" ultimately will be a rather amazing and unexpected  (train)ride  for the senses. Stay on track, CLINT !
